      <description>&lt;p&gt;I can&amp;rsquo;t stand my poor math anymore, and start to re-learn math from calculus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This notes will record some formulas and anything intersting about calculus.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;trigonometry&#34;&gt;Trigonometry&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&#34;astc-method&#34;&gt;ASTC method&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;col-12 col-xl-9 col-lg-12 container-fluid mx-0 px-0 mx-auto&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;d-block mx-auto&#34; href=&#34;https://i.imgur.com/6gLcT4l.png&#34; data-fancybox=&#34;gallery&#34; data-caption=&#34;ASTC method&#34;&gt;
        &lt;img class=&#34;mw-100 mt-2 px-0 rounded d-block mx-auto&#34; src=&#34;https://i.imgur.com/6gLcT4l.png&#34; /&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

    
    &lt;p class=&#39;mb-5 mt-2 text-center font-weight-bold&#39;&gt;ASTC method&lt;/p&gt;
    
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;h3 id=&#34;trig-identities&#34;&gt;Trig Identities&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$$
\begin{array}{l}
cos^2(x) + sin^2(x) =1 \\&lt;br /&gt;
1 + tan^2(x) = sec^2(x)
\end{array}
$$&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$$
\begin{array}{ll}
sin(A+B) &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; sin(A)cos(B) + cos(A)sin(B) \\&lt;br /&gt;
cos(A+B) &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; cos(A)cos(B) - sin(A)sin(B) \\&lt;br /&gt;
sin(2x)  &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; 2 sin(x) cos(x) \\&lt;br /&gt;
cos(2x)  &amp;amp; = &amp;amp; 2 cos^2(x) - 1  = 1 - 2 sin^2(x)
\end{array}
$$&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
